  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is aim to evaluate usefulness of the perioperative monitoring of skin perfusion
      pressure as an indicator of perpheral perfusion in patients undergoing on-pump cardiac
      surgery. Association of the intraoperative and postoperative 6hr skin perfusion pressure with
      perioperative serum lactate level is going to be assessed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
